WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.010 --> 00:00:07.822
Dear young people, today in the church
we commemorate Saint Joseph the Worker.

00:00:07.822 --> 00:00:10.442
Today is also Labor Day.

00:00:10.442 --> 00:00:18.302
Work is not a punishment, but rather the
purpose of our existence and our lives.

00:00:18.302 --> 00:00:25.638
Because if you look at the first
pages of the Holy Scripture, God gives

00:00:25.638 --> 00:00:29.306
us the command to work, to create.

00:00:29.306 --> 00:00:35.595
However, among the seven deadly
sins, there is one sin called what?

00:00:36.175 --> 00:00:40.247
The last one of these seven is sloth.

00:00:40.247 --> 00:00:47.882
So, if the Lord has given us the
grace to work, and many today desire

00:00:47.882 --> 00:00:53.991
an easy life, a comfortable luxury,
when you open social media, everyone

00:00:53.991 --> 00:00:57.554
seems to be living the high life.

00:00:57.554 --> 00:01:00.099
But no one is working.

00:01:00.099 --> 00:01:02.644
I warn you, young people.

00:01:02.644 --> 00:01:10.280
So, is it in your hearts to become
something overnight, to earn, to be rich,

00:01:10.280 --> 00:01:18.425
or do you do everything for the glory
of God, for the greater glory of God?

00:01:19.245 --> 00:01:26.101
A dangerous trend being imposed
on you today is that you are

00:01:26.101 --> 00:01:28.958
not very interested in work.

00:01:28.958 --> 00:01:33.529
When I say work, what do I mean?

00:01:33.529 --> 00:01:36.957
Not just jobs in some company.

00:01:36.957 --> 00:01:43.814
We can talk about the spirit of
laziness, the sin of laziness

00:01:43.814 --> 00:01:47.242
that extends to our entire life.

00:01:47.242 --> 00:01:52.385
Spiritual, let's say material,
and let's also say aesthetic.

00:01:53.305 --> 00:01:58.706
How many people have neglected their lives
due to laziness, whether financially,

00:01:58.706 --> 00:02:00.957
spiritually, or even their appearance?

00:02:00.957 --> 00:02:06.358
But how many of you young
people today even take this sin

00:02:06.358 --> 00:02:09.059
seriously, and it is very evident.

00:02:09.059 --> 00:02:10.859
Now, look at this.

00:02:10.859 --> 00:02:18.512
If you go to see when Jesus speaks in
the 25th chapter of one of the Gospels,

00:02:18.512 --> 00:02:25.714
He talks about the end of the world
and that He will come to separate those

00:02:25.714 --> 00:02:29.315
on the left and those on the right.

00:02:30.535 --> 00:02:36.465
And those who will be on the left will
go to hell, while those on the right

00:02:36.465 --> 00:02:38.907
will go to the kingdom of heaven.

00:02:38.907 --> 00:02:41.000
And I find that very interesting.

00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:45.884
The criteria for those who will
go to hell are the same as for

00:02:45.884 --> 00:02:47.977
those who will go to heaven.

00:02:47.977 --> 00:02:52.861
Jesus tells them a parable: When
I was hungry, you did this for me.

00:02:52.861 --> 00:02:56.001
When I was thirsty, you did this for me.

00:02:56.001 --> 00:02:59.489
When I was in prison, you did this for me.

00:02:59.769 --> 00:03:06.391
So he says, you on the right who have
done this, will go into eternal life.

00:03:06.391 --> 00:03:11.770
However, he says, calling those
on the left, when I was hungry you

00:03:11.770 --> 00:03:18.392
didn't give me food, when I was in
prison, when I was thirsty, and so on.

00:03:18.392 --> 00:03:25.013
So he says that we will be judged by
what we haven't done, and many things

00:03:25.013 --> 00:03:27.910
today we don't do out of laziness.

00:03:28.870 --> 00:03:31.228
Just look at our prayers.

00:03:31.228 --> 00:03:37.360
We don't feel like going to church,
we don't feel like praying, we

00:03:37.360 --> 00:03:40.190
don't feel like doing good deeds.

00:03:40.190 --> 00:03:43.491
So much is missed out of laziness.

00:03:43.491 --> 00:03:50.566
And here it says that many will end
up in hell because they missed out

00:03:50.566 --> 00:03:53.868
or were too lazy to do something.

00:03:53.868 --> 00:04:00.943
So, there are many today who, in any
area you look at, are doing things

00:04:00.943 --> 00:04:02.829
half-heartedly or are negligent.

00:04:03.950 --> 00:04:11.025
If you have a job at a company, if
you are in a church, if you have a

00:04:11.025 --> 00:04:16.922
role in the church, if you are part
of a church community, and you are

00:04:16.922 --> 00:04:21.639
doing things only mediocrely, that
also falls into the category of sin.

00:04:21.639 --> 00:04:25.964
If you are negligently doing the
tasks you are responsible for,

00:04:25.964 --> 00:04:28.715
it is also a category of sin.

00:04:28.715 --> 00:04:33.826
Today, as we remember Joseph the
Worker, Joseph who is, in general, Saint

00:04:33.826 --> 00:04:36.185
Joseph, an example to all husbands.

00:04:36.945 --> 00:04:38.795
So, Joseph was selfless.

00:04:38.795 --> 00:04:44.348
He didn't work for himself, think
for himself, or fight for himself.

00:04:44.348 --> 00:04:48.049
He dedicated his life to Mary and Jesus.

00:04:48.049 --> 00:04:54.065
But what examples do we have today
of many men, many fathers who

00:04:54.065 --> 00:04:58.692
should be leaders and selflessly
give themselves to their families?

00:04:58.692 --> 00:05:00.080
Where are they?

00:05:00.080 --> 00:05:01.468
Where are they?

00:05:01.468 --> 00:05:07.946
If we look at the example of Saint
Joseph's life, he selflessly gave and

00:05:07.946 --> 00:05:11.185
sacrificed himself for others out of love.

00:05:13.270 --> 00:05:18.439
And today we have modern families,
modern husbands, modern Josephs, who

00:05:18.439 --> 00:05:25.018
will send everything to the house,
money and all, but they are not there.

00:05:25.018 --> 00:05:27.837
There is no father, no husband.

00:05:27.837 --> 00:05:33.946
And the Lord requires that
everything we do, we do out of love.

00:05:33.946 --> 00:05:39.116
And that is why Saint
Joseph is an example to us.

00:05:39.116 --> 00:05:41.935
Not to turn things towards ourselves.

00:05:41.935 --> 00:05:46.635
And believe me, laziness brings
great disorder into our lives.

00:05:46.835 --> 00:05:49.104
And you know what's even sadder?

00:05:49.104 --> 00:05:51.751
That many people admit they are lazy.

00:05:51.751 --> 00:05:55.911
Every third confession we hear starts
with all those spiritual dramas,

00:05:55.911 --> 00:06:00.827
about how they would like to change
their life, but then when they

00:06:00.827 --> 00:06:02.718
leave, everything stays the same.

00:06:02.718 --> 00:06:07.634
Well, it will stay the same
if you don't snap out of it.

00:06:07.634 --> 00:06:10.660
If you don't decide to stop being lazy.

00:06:10.800 --> 00:06:14.252
And why do many people publicly
admit that they are lazy?

00:06:14.252 --> 00:06:16.135
Precisely so that they are tolerated.

00:06:16.135 --> 00:06:18.645
So that no one expects them to change.

00:06:18.645 --> 00:06:22.097
"I am lazy." Look, some people
don't work their entire lives.

00:06:22.097 --> 00:06:26.177
They do nothing at work, nothing for their
spirituality, nothing for their family.

00:06:26.177 --> 00:06:30.257
They are lazy, set in their ways,
and they don't just admit it.

00:06:30.257 --> 00:06:30.884
They don't.

00:06:30.884 --> 00:06:34.650
It's a psychological fact that
they admit it publicly so that you

00:06:34.650 --> 00:06:36.220
don't expect anything from them.

00:06:36.420 --> 00:06:41.088
And we, as a society, come to
terms with and accept such people,

00:06:41.088 --> 00:06:45.038
saying, you know, he's lazy,
don't count on him for anything.

00:06:45.038 --> 00:06:50.065
But we forget that this is categorized
as one of the seven deadly sins.

00:06:50.065 --> 00:06:52.578
And it brings a lot of disorder.

00:06:52.578 --> 00:06:57.606
It's fascinating to me, when we talk about
spirituality, how lazy we Christians are.

00:06:57.606 --> 00:06:59.760
And that's why we stay silent.

00:06:59.760 --> 00:07:03.710
Don't seek changes in spiritual
life in the church if you're

00:07:03.710 --> 00:07:05.865
too lazy to lift a finger.

00:07:05.925 --> 00:07:10.753
Prayer is hard for you, getting up is
hard, reading the Bible is hard, going to

00:07:10.753 --> 00:07:13.167
Mass is hard, everything is hard for you.

00:07:13.167 --> 00:07:14.978
Then admit that you are lazy.

00:07:14.978 --> 00:07:17.392
And not just any lazy,
but spiritually lazy.

00:07:17.392 --> 00:07:21.617
Sometimes I see it in churches, and
you can tell someone had to force

00:07:21.617 --> 00:07:24.937
them to come, whether it was their
grandmother, wife, or husband.

00:07:24.937 --> 00:07:30.067
You can see it on their face in church,
they don't want to open their mouth, they

00:07:30.067 --> 00:07:35.500
don't want to sing, they don't want to be
there, they can’t wait for it to be over.

00:07:36.460 --> 00:07:39.345
And that is the spirit of laziness.

00:07:39.345 --> 00:07:43.467
And what can God do for us in that state?

00:07:43.467 --> 00:07:43.879
Nothing.

00:07:43.879 --> 00:07:48.414
There's a simple truth when you
see how people look, especially

00:07:48.414 --> 00:07:50.887
if you can enter their space.

00:07:50.887 --> 00:07:54.597
Because the space says a
lot about our spirituality.

00:07:54.597 --> 00:07:59.131
What is your house like, your
room, not just your nails.

00:07:59.131 --> 00:08:05.315
It's not about what we show on the
outside, but what your house is like.

00:08:05.335 --> 00:08:10.839
If in your room, the room where
you live, young man or young woman,

00:08:10.839 --> 00:08:15.558
or any of us, there is disorder,
your spirituality is no better.

00:08:15.558 --> 00:08:21.849
If it's normal for you to look at that
table where you can't put anything down

00:08:21.849 --> 00:08:26.567
because it's cluttered with everything,
including bread, if your room is chaotic,

00:08:26.567 --> 00:08:29.320
what kind of spirit can settle there?

00:08:31.010 --> 00:08:32.748
There is no ventilation.

00:08:32.748 --> 00:08:34.921
It reflects our inner state.

00:08:34.921 --> 00:08:36.659
That's the plain truth.

00:08:36.659 --> 00:08:41.440
When people neglect themselves physically,
and then someone complains, "I'm alone,

00:08:41.440 --> 00:08:45.352
no one wants me." Well, who will want you?

00:08:45.352 --> 00:08:47.960
Get yourself together, for God's sake.

00:08:51.365 --> 00:08:54.395
The spirit of laziness,
I won't wash my hair.

00:08:54.395 --> 00:08:58.436
When I see young men coming to
church in tracksuits, come on,

00:08:58.436 --> 00:09:00.793
you're going to church, not the gym.

00:09:00.793 --> 00:09:05.844
You couldn't spare five minutes for God's
house to dress up and come to church

00:09:05.844 --> 00:09:07.865
looking decent, not in a tracksuit.

00:09:10.895 --> 00:09:13.046
You can see it all.

00:09:13.046 --> 00:09:17.780
That's why I say we project
what's inside us, what's important

00:09:17.780 --> 00:09:19.931
to us, through our appearance.

00:09:19.931 --> 00:09:22.513
You can see it all clearly.

00:09:22.513 --> 00:09:24.235
Now, you see, everything

00:09:28.615 --> 00:09:31.923
If you look at laziness, it's very clear.

00:09:31.923 --> 00:09:37.299
King Solomon notes that the one
who is negligent in his work is

00:09:37.299 --> 00:09:40.193
a brother to the one who wastes.

00:09:40.193 --> 00:09:42.261
Saint Paul goes even further.

00:09:42.261 --> 00:09:48.464
Saint Paul says that the one who
does not want to work should not eat.

00:09:48.464 --> 00:09:49.705
Should not eat.

00:09:49.705 --> 00:09:54.254
How ridiculous is it today that
people in Croatia complain that

00:09:54.254 --> 00:09:59.630
they don't have jobs, that this
and that, how is there no work?

00:10:00.345 --> 00:10:03.499
But we are lazy, saying there are no jobs.

00:10:03.499 --> 00:10:07.004
How do foreigners find jobs
in Croatia, but we don't?

00:10:07.004 --> 00:10:08.406
Because we are lazy.

00:10:08.406 --> 00:10:10.860
But why am I bringing this up?

00:10:10.860 --> 00:10:12.963
There's one thing we Croatians do.

00:10:12.963 --> 00:10:16.819
We would rather say that life
in Croatia is a disaster.

00:10:16.819 --> 00:10:22.077
I watched an interview the other day, and
all the young people were talking about

00:10:22.077 --> 00:10:24.881
Croatia as if it were a chaotic country.

00:10:24.881 --> 00:10:28.736
No future, better salaries elsewhere,
we can't find jobs, maybe it's

00:10:28.736 --> 00:10:30.840
this way, maybe it's that way.

00:10:32.590 --> 00:10:36.489
Let's compare the second picture,
how foreigners can find work.

00:10:36.489 --> 00:10:41.558
Either we are lazy or we spend
the whole day crocheting, or we

00:10:41.558 --> 00:10:45.847
are playing games and doing other
things, letting time pass by.

00:10:45.847 --> 00:10:49.746
So, work makes sense to
others, but not to us.

00:10:49.746 --> 00:10:55.205
Should we call it by its real
name, that we are a bit lazy?

00:10:55.205 --> 00:10:59.105
There's a good quote if
you go to Proverbs 22:13.

00:10:59.105 --> 00:11:06.346
A line from the proverb goes like this:
The sluggard says, "There is a lion

00:11:06.346 --> 00:11:13.588
outside! I will be killed in the public
square!" So, the sluggard says, "There is

00:11:13.588 --> 00:11:20.829
a lion outside! I will be killed in the
public square!" The sluggard is justifying

00:11:20.829 --> 00:11:24.209
not going outside because of the lion.

00:11:24.209 --> 00:11:30.968
It would be more accurate to say,
"The coward is afraid to go outside

00:11:30.968 --> 00:11:38.209
because there is a lion." What does
this have to do with being a sluggard?

00:11:38.329 --> 00:11:41.435
So, we see what he's doing.

00:11:41.435 --> 00:11:44.022
He's looking for an excuse.

00:11:44.022 --> 00:11:50.750
He won't go outside to work because
then there's that feeling of fear.

00:11:50.750 --> 00:11:56.960
But the saying starts with "the
sluggard says." So, the problem is

00:11:56.960 --> 00:12:02.135
that many times we invent different
circumstances to avoid working.

00:12:02.135 --> 00:12:06.275
Different circumstances to avoid
working on ourselves spiritually,

00:12:06.275 --> 00:12:09.380
materially, or in any other way.

00:12:09.380 --> 00:12:11.450
And that's not good.

00:12:11.450 --> 00:12:13.731
That won't help us grow.

00:12:13.731 --> 00:12:18.294
We are called, as I said, work is a gift.

00:12:18.294 --> 00:12:25.139
We are called to create, to strive, to
fight, to appreciate, not to be lazy.

00:12:25.139 --> 00:12:30.615
And when you look at it, our
motivation should be that everything

00:12:30.615 --> 00:12:34.722
we do, we do for the glory of God.

00:12:34.722 --> 00:12:36.547
That God is glorified.

00:12:36.547 --> 00:12:42.480
We must not be motivated by personal
laziness, money, or a comfortable life.

00:12:42.945 --> 00:12:45.350
Because we can't all achieve that.

00:12:45.350 --> 00:12:50.161
Some have ordinary jobs, some have
serious ones, some this, some that,

00:12:50.161 --> 00:12:55.373
but whatever we do, it's important
that it's for the glory of God.

00:12:55.373 --> 00:13:00.985
Sirach 33:23 calls us to be the
best in everything we do and says

00:13:00.985 --> 00:13:06.999
this: "In all your works be the
master, and do not let your honor be

00:13:06.999 --> 00:13:09.405
stained." The saints tell us this.

00:13:09.855 --> 00:13:18.680
And whatever you do, whether in
word or deed, do it all in the name

00:13:18.680 --> 00:13:25.740
of the Lord Jesus, giving thanks
to God the Father through him.

00:13:25.740 --> 00:13:29.270
Remember David when he killed Goliath.

00:13:29.270 --> 00:13:32.800
Overnight, he became a national hero.

00:13:32.800 --> 00:13:38.684
His rise to fame was instant
when he killed Goliath.

00:13:38.684 --> 00:13:43.391
The whole nation bowed
to him, giving thanks.

00:13:43.391 --> 00:13:50.451
Do you think David truly achieved
that moment when he took the

00:13:50.451 --> 00:13:52.805
sling and killed Goliath?

00:13:54.745 --> 00:14:01.813
What you young people see today on social
media, when you scroll through all those

00:14:01.813 --> 00:14:06.996
beautiful social networks, as I do,
everyone wants quick success overnight.

00:14:06.996 --> 00:14:11.708
Everyone suddenly wants
to get rich and be on top.

00:14:11.708 --> 00:14:16.420
It's sad that many people advertise
themselves cheaply to become

00:14:16.420 --> 00:14:18.305
popular and earn something.

00:14:18.305 --> 00:14:20.131
I call that modern begging.

00:14:20.131 --> 00:14:20.861
Tap, tap.

00:14:20.861 --> 00:14:25.974
Those of you who follow TikTok know
what it means in a live stream.

00:14:25.974 --> 00:14:26.704
Tap, tap.

00:14:26.704 --> 00:14:27.800
It means donate.

00:14:27.800 --> 00:14:32.913
So, it's easier for me to spend hours
saying tap, tap, i.e., donate to

00:14:32.913 --> 00:14:35.835
me, than to actually get a real job.

00:14:39.045 --> 00:14:45.997
Isn't it a bit strange, dear girls
and boys, when you see on social

00:14:45.997 --> 00:14:51.460
media, people your age, young men
and women, boasting about apartments,

00:14:51.460 --> 00:14:53.943
cars, luxurious outings, and travels?

00:14:53.943 --> 00:14:59.406
How, my dear, can you achieve
that at 19-20 years old?

00:14:59.406 --> 00:14:59.902
How?

00:14:59.902 --> 00:15:04.372
For which company do you
work, for which father?

00:15:04.372 --> 00:15:07.848
Or are you in some political party?

00:15:07.848 --> 00:15:08.345
How?

00:15:08.345 --> 00:15:09.197
Tell me.

00:15:09.197 --> 00:15:10.902
What does that mean?

00:15:10.902 --> 00:15:13.034
That it's all a lie.

00:15:13.034 --> 00:15:18.149
That they are just lazy people
who earn money in a simple,

00:15:18.149 --> 00:15:19.854
sneaky, somewhat cheap way.

00:15:19.854 --> 00:15:25.823
I won't comment on how, but I'm
telling you this to let you know

00:15:25.823 --> 00:15:28.380
not to dream about such things.

00:15:28.380 --> 00:15:29.659
It's a lie.

00:15:29.659 --> 00:15:33.496
The right path is to be like Saint Joseph.

00:15:33.496 --> 00:15:39.464
The man was a carpenter, he didn't
reject his job, he valued his work,

00:15:39.464 --> 00:15:44.579
and through such hard manual physical
labor, he provided for his family.

00:15:44.920 --> 00:15:49.882
He didn't dream of unattainable
dreams but did what he was capable of.

00:15:49.882 --> 00:15:55.226
So why are you, dear young people,
being pushed to dream of some grand

00:15:55.226 --> 00:16:00.570
ideal life when you know you're not
in the category that can have it?

00:16:00.570 --> 00:16:05.150
And then you enter a state of
frustration, disappointment, and give up.

00:16:05.150 --> 00:16:05.914
But why?

00:16:05.914 --> 00:16:10.494
You are all healthy and normal
enough to earn a living and

00:16:10.494 --> 00:16:12.785
not be a burden to anyone.

00:16:13.545 --> 00:16:20.133
Why do you need to have the best car,
the best apartment, or anything else?

00:16:20.133 --> 00:16:22.768
Work within your capabilities and limits.

00:16:22.768 --> 00:16:23.207
Understand?

00:16:23.207 --> 00:16:28.478
Don't fall for that false propaganda;
appreciate what you are capable of.

00:16:28.478 --> 00:16:32.431
Even if it's physical
labor, whatever it may be.

00:16:32.431 --> 00:16:36.384
And why do I keep coming back to David?

00:16:36.384 --> 00:16:42.093
He didn't achieve fame overnight just
because he slung a stone and killed

00:16:42.093 --> 00:16:44.290
Goliath, becoming a national hero.

00:16:44.510 --> 00:16:47.816
Let's go back and think
about how he succeeded.

00:16:47.816 --> 00:16:53.327
And how can you, as a young girl
or a young boy, succeed as well?

00:16:53.327 --> 00:16:55.899
David was sent to tend the sheep.

00:16:55.899 --> 00:16:59.205
He didn't learn the skill of
slingshot shooting overnight.

00:16:59.205 --> 00:17:02.512
Have you ever held a slingshot as a child?

00:17:02.512 --> 00:17:05.451
We did, we played with slingshots as kids.

00:17:05.451 --> 00:17:09.493
But the more we played, the
more we became, let's say,

00:17:09.493 --> 00:17:11.329
capable of hitting the target.

00:17:14.274 --> 00:17:19.109
He was tending the sheep, alone
with the sheep in some desert.

00:17:19.109 --> 00:17:23.138
No audience, no protection,
no one to monitor your work,

00:17:23.138 --> 00:17:25.153
what you are doing there.

00:17:25.153 --> 00:17:27.570
But David was tending the sheep.

00:17:27.570 --> 00:17:34.017
And you will find in the Holy Scriptures
where a few times a bear and other

00:17:34.017 --> 00:17:36.434
animals came and attacked the sheep.

00:17:36.434 --> 00:17:39.254
What could David say in that situation?

00:17:39.405 --> 00:17:40.578
As a boy.

00:17:40.578 --> 00:17:46.053
Mind you, David is a boy, tending
sheep, and when a bear or some

00:17:46.053 --> 00:17:49.965
dangerous animal comes, he could
say, well, it won't economically

00:17:49.965 --> 00:17:53.485
ruin me if it takes one or two sheep.

00:17:53.485 --> 00:17:58.178
You know, it specifically says
that he rolled up his sleeves and

00:17:58.178 --> 00:18:00.133
fought with wild animals barehanded.

00:18:00.133 --> 00:18:04.045
So, as a boy, he was already
practicing something, fighting.

00:18:04.340 --> 00:18:09.934
He used a sling, physically fought
with wild animals so that one day,

00:18:09.934 --> 00:18:14.668
with that experience, he could
stand before Goliath and kill him.

00:18:14.668 --> 00:18:15.098
Understand?

00:18:15.098 --> 00:18:20.693
That's why you can't skip this
part in your job, career, or work.

00:18:20.693 --> 00:18:22.844
It starts with small things.

00:18:22.844 --> 00:18:25.426
You practice with small things first.

00:18:25.426 --> 00:18:29.300
You can't immediately jump
to being a national hero.

00:18:29.900 --> 00:18:32.308
The greatest wealth, but you go.

00:18:32.308 --> 00:18:35.117
And what is even more interesting here?

00:18:35.117 --> 00:18:37.927
Well, David didn't know what awaited him.

00:18:37.927 --> 00:18:42.743
And what he did, he could
have even let a sheep die.

00:18:42.743 --> 00:18:46.757
No one would have seen
it, no one was present.

00:18:46.757 --> 00:18:49.165
But no, as I said earlier.

00:18:49.165 --> 00:18:52.777
He did everything for
the greater glory of God.

00:18:52.777 --> 00:18:54.383
Because remember Psalm 23.

00:18:54.383 --> 00:18:56.390
The Lord is my shepherd.

00:18:56.390 --> 00:19:02.811
David surely had that in mind, Lord my
shepherd, I am doing this job to guard

00:19:02.811 --> 00:19:09.635
the flock, I will defend it as much as
I know and can with all my strength.

00:19:11.335 --> 00:19:16.223
There is no reward, no audience,
no applause, he is alone with the

00:19:16.223 --> 00:19:21.111
sheep, but the Lord sees everything,
the Lord is my shepherd, Psalm 23.

00:19:21.111 --> 00:19:26.375
That's it, my dears, when we learn
to work and handle tasks, things, and

00:19:26.375 --> 00:19:30.887
situations like that, always keeping
in mind that God is watching us.

00:19:30.887 --> 00:19:32.391
Practice in small things.

00:19:32.391 --> 00:19:35.399
Then God will perform
a miracle through you.

00:19:35.909 --> 00:19:41.532
God will be glorified through
you if you view things this way.

00:19:41.532 --> 00:19:43.875
Strive to make it so.

00:19:43.875 --> 00:19:47.623
Saint Joseph is a role model for many.

00:19:47.623 --> 00:19:50.903
Why else is he a role model?

00:19:50.903 --> 00:19:52.309
He was obedient.

00:19:52.309 --> 00:19:53.714
Obedient to God.

00:19:53.714 --> 00:20:00.743
Remember all those situations when he
was told to marry Mary, then when he was

00:20:00.743 --> 00:20:08.240
told to take Mary and Jesus and flee,
and then when he was told to return.

00:20:08.740 --> 00:20:09.861
To be obedient.

00:20:09.861 --> 00:20:13.224
To be obedient to what God wants from you.

00:20:13.224 --> 00:20:17.709
And that's why it's very important
for us to examine ourselves as

00:20:17.709 --> 00:20:20.325
well, but do we listen to God?

00:20:20.325 --> 00:20:25.558
Or do we listen to our feelings of
laziness, not wanting to do anything?

00:20:25.558 --> 00:20:31.164
When I see you young people, 25, 30
years old, not wanting to play sports,

00:20:31.164 --> 00:20:37.517
not wanting to do this or that, as
they used to say in my village, when I

00:20:37.517 --> 00:20:40.507
see how you walk, you know right away.

00:20:40.507 --> 00:20:46.113
If you've already lost the strength for
life, for the fight, if you don't feel

00:20:46.113 --> 00:20:48.730
like doing anything now, when will you?

00:20:48.730 --> 00:20:50.699
When will you then?

00:20:50.699 --> 00:20:56.115
If we have now settled for
mediocrity and don't care about

00:20:56.115 --> 00:20:58.577
things, that's really not good.

00:20:58.577 --> 00:21:03.993
And that spirit of laziness
permeates all areas of our lives.

00:21:03.993 --> 00:21:04.978
Through everything.

00:21:04.978 --> 00:21:10.394
I said, from the spiritual to
the physical, to whatever you

00:21:10.394 --> 00:21:12.856
want, and that's not good.

00:21:12.856 --> 00:21:16.302
Let's guard against
the spirit of laziness.

00:21:16.302 --> 00:21:23.688
If you feel lazy, if you don't feel like
doing something, whether it's fighting for

00:21:23.688 --> 00:21:26.150
life, praying spiritually, or whatever.

00:21:27.650 --> 00:21:31.184
I always say, look, engagement
in the church for God.

00:21:31.184 --> 00:21:35.425
When I say engagement in the
church, I don't mean you're doing

00:21:35.425 --> 00:21:39.666
me a favor, but that we're all
collectively striving for God's cause.

00:21:39.666 --> 00:21:41.434
People don't feel like it.

00:21:41.434 --> 00:21:44.615
People don't feel like coming
to rehearsals, people don't

00:21:44.615 --> 00:21:47.442
feel like practicing, people
don't feel like serving.

00:21:47.442 --> 00:21:48.149
They don't.

00:21:48.149 --> 00:21:50.270
And then we all become sluggish.

00:21:50.810 --> 00:21:55.927
And these days we've been hearing
about the revelation that says

00:21:55.927 --> 00:21:58.253
you're either cold or hot.

00:21:58.253 --> 00:22:02.906
If you're lukewarm, I'll
spit you out of my mouth.

00:22:02.906 --> 00:22:04.302
So we fight.

00:22:04.302 --> 00:22:06.628
Saint Joseph was a worker.

00:22:06.628 --> 00:22:13.141
A worker, he was a leader, and now I'm
especially addressing you men, these

00:22:13.141 --> 00:22:20.120
are two very important things, to be
a worker, but also to be a leader.

00:22:20.120 --> 00:22:25.703
Not a leader like today's leaders,
but a leader in your family,

00:22:25.703 --> 00:22:28.495
to take care of your family.

00:22:28.855 --> 00:22:37.453
Well, you men can't just sit back; our
role is to provide, to work, to fight.

00:22:37.453 --> 00:22:39.603
Especially for the family.

00:22:39.603 --> 00:22:45.514
We men can't allow ourselves
to get married and then let

00:22:45.514 --> 00:22:48.202
the woman carry the household.

00:22:48.202 --> 00:22:53.038
The woman shouldn't have
to take care of everything.

00:22:53.038 --> 00:22:53.576
Fight.

00:22:53.576 --> 00:22:54.113
Work.

00:22:54.113 --> 00:22:55.725
Start with something.

00:22:55.725 --> 00:22:56.800
Stop complaining.

00:22:56.800 --> 00:23:02.175
Look, many have fallen into
many sins because of laziness.

00:23:02.445 --> 00:23:07.399
Many young people today are
dependent due to laziness.

00:23:07.399 --> 00:23:11.804
Dependent on betting shops,
dependent on other things.

00:23:11.804 --> 00:23:14.006
All because of laziness.

00:23:14.006 --> 00:23:15.107
Remember David.

00:23:15.107 --> 00:23:18.961
There's even a quote I found somewhere.

00:23:18.961 --> 00:23:23.916
So, in 2 Samuel, chapter 11, it says this.

00:23:23.916 --> 00:23:30.523
King David, who committed a sin out
of laziness, out of unemployment.

00:23:30.523 --> 00:23:38.231
It says this, at the beginning of
the next year, at the time when

00:23:38.231 --> 00:23:47.040
kings go out to war, David sent Joab
and his men, all of Israel, to war.

00:23:47.740 --> 00:23:53.400
So, he should have gone too, but
he stayed at home and sent others.

00:23:53.400 --> 00:23:58.251
And then, in the meantime, the story
continues: after he had breakfast

00:23:58.251 --> 00:24:02.698
and completed his morning hygiene
routine, he was walking on the

00:24:02.698 --> 00:24:05.124
terrace and saw another man's wife.

00:24:05.124 --> 00:24:08.359
He called her to him, and they sinned.

00:24:08.359 --> 00:24:13.614
Then, to cover it all up, he
wanted to kill her husband and

00:24:13.614 --> 00:24:19.274
put him on the front line to die
so that it wouldn't be discovered

00:24:19.274 --> 00:24:22.105
that he had sinned with his wife.

00:24:23.215 --> 00:24:25.600
All out of laziness and boredom.

00:24:25.600 --> 00:24:30.768
But if he had gone to war
with the soldiers he sent, he

00:24:30.768 --> 00:24:32.755
wouldn't have committed this sin.

00:24:32.755 --> 00:24:38.321
How many times do saints warn us
that if we don't keep ourselves busy,

00:24:38.321 --> 00:24:41.103
the devil will find work for us.

00:24:41.103 --> 00:24:47.066
That's why I tell you that many addictions
in young people develop out of boredom.

00:24:47.066 --> 00:24:51.837
If you don't work, if you laze
around, what else will you

00:24:51.837 --> 00:24:56.210
do but start playing games or
binge-watching series out of boredom?

00:24:58.090 --> 00:25:05.284
Then a bit of gambling, a bit of betting,
a bit of this, a bit of that, and

00:25:05.284 --> 00:25:07.283
addiction unconsciously sucks you in.

00:25:07.283 --> 00:25:09.681
Addiction unconsciously
takes control of you.

00:25:09.681 --> 00:25:14.877
Believe me, a large number of young
people today have problems with this.

00:25:14.877 --> 00:25:17.675
So fight and look for a job.

00:25:17.675 --> 00:25:19.674
Get active in every area.

00:25:19.674 --> 00:25:24.071
Do something for your paycheck, and
especially, I want to emphasize,

00:25:24.071 --> 00:25:25.669
for this spiritual laziness.

00:25:25.970 --> 00:25:28.333
I see the mess here.

00:25:28.333 --> 00:25:33.534
When I see how much disorder and
chaotic situations some people

00:25:33.534 --> 00:25:38.262
have in their hearts because of
that laziness, it's unbelievable.

00:25:38.262 --> 00:25:40.626
Let me emphasize one thing.

00:25:40.626 --> 00:25:46.772
Anyone who feels that spiritual laziness,
don't dramatize, don't say "I don't feel

00:25:46.772 --> 00:25:50.554
like it" and so on, but start cleaning.

00:25:50.554 --> 00:25:55.754
Start cleaning, don't brag about
it, just start cleaning your heart.

00:25:56.325 --> 00:26:01.804
Just like you have a physical room that
needs to be cleaned and organized, a

00:26:01.804 --> 00:26:03.996
closet, organize your heart as well.

00:26:03.996 --> 00:26:05.823
There's no use in complaining.

00:26:05.823 --> 00:26:10.572
So, against laziness, the only effective
remedy can be a decision: today I

00:26:10.572 --> 00:26:12.764
start cleaning my heart, my thoughts.

00:26:12.764 --> 00:26:13.495
Clean, resolve.

00:26:13.495 --> 00:26:19.705
If you keep saying "I don't feel like
it, I don't feel like it," then be quiet.

00:26:19.705 --> 00:26:24.455
But the only cure is to start
working and cleaning in that area.

00:26:24.575 --> 00:26:27.377
Well, we are fighting against
the spirit of laziness.

00:26:27.377 --> 00:26:31.736
And to you, dear young people, I
open your eyes and encourage you to

00:26:31.736 --> 00:26:33.604
fight against laziness in every area.

00:26:33.604 --> 00:26:38.275
How beautiful it is, what joy you get
when you create, when you earn something

00:26:38.275 --> 00:26:42.011
through hard work, and when you fight,
when you achieve spiritual growth.

00:26:42.011 --> 00:26:43.256
Just look at spirituality.

00:26:43.256 --> 00:26:47.927
It's normal for you young people who go
to church, while many are out barbecuing

00:26:47.927 --> 00:26:51.975
and enjoying themselves today, you have
come to church again, which I appreciate.

00:26:52.355 --> 00:26:57.820
So, in a way, it shows that you care
about nurturing your spiritual life.

00:26:57.820 --> 00:27:00.553
Because you can have a barbecue anytime.

00:27:00.553 --> 00:27:06.018
It's so important to fight and not
let that spirit of laziness take over.

00:27:06.018 --> 00:27:11.874
Otherwise, you'll remain sluggish, and
many of you are at a stage where in a

00:27:11.874 --> 00:27:17.729
year or two or three, you'll be getting
married and will need to support others.

00:27:17.729 --> 00:27:22.164
And if you are the remedy but
haven't sorted yourself out yet,

00:27:22.164 --> 00:27:26.969
and then you have children, a wife,
and other worries, it won't work.

00:27:26.969 --> 00:27:32.512
But you see, when you are spiritually
engaged, like you young people here in the

00:27:32.512 --> 00:27:35.099
church, you fight, a special grace comes.

00:27:35.099 --> 00:27:36.577
A special joy comes.

00:27:36.577 --> 00:27:39.903
It's not that we are
suffering, to be clear.

00:27:39.903 --> 00:27:45.447
When we oppose laziness, it's not that
we are victims and it's hard for us.

00:27:45.447 --> 00:27:51.360
Here you are, young in the church, you
fight, you live in purity, oh poor you.

00:27:51.480 --> 00:27:54.946
We do everything for the
greater glory of God.

00:27:54.946 --> 00:27:58.798
So, it's nice when you create
something, work on something,

00:27:58.798 --> 00:28:01.110
when you've put in the effort.

00:28:01.110 --> 00:28:06.502
And this is what's important, what
the Lord gave to the first humans in

00:28:06.502 --> 00:28:12.280
the Book of Genesis: the duty to work,
to create, to manage, to even name

00:28:12.280 --> 00:28:14.592
the animals, because God trusts us.

00:28:14.592 --> 00:28:20.370
And besides that faith that God has in
us, let's also have faith in ourselves.

00:28:20.610 --> 00:28:22.798
Don't declare yourself incapable.

00:28:22.798 --> 00:28:23.892
That's dangerous.

00:28:23.892 --> 00:28:28.269
When someone declares themselves
incapable, you're not incapable.

00:28:28.269 --> 00:28:31.552
You just need a little push.

00:28:31.552 --> 00:28:34.835
You just need a little nudge.

00:28:34.835 --> 00:28:39.212
And to you, parents, what can I say?

00:28:39.212 --> 00:28:46.872
Don't create a luxurious environment and
nest for your children to grow up in.

00:28:46.872 --> 00:28:50.155
Let them struggle, don't create invalids.

00:28:50.845 --> 00:28:56.288
Don't create invalids so that your
son, at 35 or 40 years old, still

00:28:56.288 --> 00:29:01.342
lives with you and hasn't lifted a
finger because you won't let him.

00:29:01.342 --> 00:29:06.397
"I'll iron for you, I'll cook for
you, I'll work for you"—that's not

00:29:06.397 --> 00:29:08.341
love, you're making him incapable.

00:29:08.341 --> 00:29:14.173
Let him fight, be his support whenever
he needs it, but this trend of "I

00:29:14.173 --> 00:29:18.838
struggled, I worked hard, so my child
doesn't have to"—that's the most

00:29:18.838 --> 00:29:21.949
dangerous thing you can do to your child.

00:29:21.949 --> 00:29:26.614
You're making it so they don't
know how to fight, so they

00:29:26.614 --> 00:29:28.170
become sluggish and average.

00:29:29.050 --> 00:29:33.248
Don't do that, you won't go wrong,
always support him from behind,

00:29:33.248 --> 00:29:35.697
but let him create on his own.

00:29:35.697 --> 00:29:39.196
Don't give him everything on
a silver platter, that's it.

00:29:39.196 --> 00:29:42.694
That's why we lack generations
today who fight, who think

00:29:42.694 --> 00:29:44.444
outside the box, who strive.

00:29:44.444 --> 00:29:48.992
Because if someone is always standing
behind you, you will never grow up.

00:29:48.992 --> 00:29:53.890
Thank God that someone from your family
can help, but don't, you will make

00:29:53.890 --> 00:29:55.990
him, believe me, incapable of life.

00:29:56.230 --> 00:29:56.830
Amen.

